 Port Elizabeth - The South African Police Service in the Nelson Mandela Bay Metro assisted by the Metro Police, Provincial Traffic, SANDF and the NMB traffic remain relentless in their continuing efforts to ensure that the lockdown regulations as stipulated in the Disaster Management Act is strictly adhered to. "Various roadblocks are held throughout the metro on a daily basis and motorists are courteously interrogated as to their movements," said police spokesperson, Capt Sandra Janse van Rensburg. "Residents were urged to shop for essential items in their respective areas thus restricting movement. "Police will continue with their operational responsibilities and has warned the communities that they will not hesitate to arrest anyone who is in contravention of the Act." She said that foot patrols are done daily throughout the metro in our endeavours to ensure that there are no pedestrians on the streets. "Visiting friends and family during lockdown is not allowed and those found flouting these regulations are arrested." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  